          <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2 mt-1">Client-Side GTM</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 mb-3">A small JavaScript snippet on your website. Sends page views and events to your sGTM server.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-blue-600 bg-blue-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            You probably already have this
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center md:flex-col">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 rotate-90 md:rotate-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Piece 2: sGTM hosting -->
        <div class="flex-1 border-2 border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-purple-50 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-4 bg-purple-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded">2</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-2 mt-1">sGTM Server</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 mb-3">A server that receives data from your client GTM and runs tags server-side. Lives on your domain (e.g. <code class="bg-purple-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">gtm.yoursite.com</code>).</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-purple-600 bg-purple-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            5-min setup via Stape.io
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center md:flex-col">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 rotate-90 md:rotate-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Piece 3: mbuzz tag -->
        <div class="flex-1 border-2 border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-green-50 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-4 bg-green-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded">3</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2 mt-1">mbuzz Tag Template</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-green-800 mb-3">A tag that runs inside your sGTM server. Sends visitor, session, and conversion data to mbuzz for attribution.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-green-600 bg-green-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            Import in 2 clicks
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bottom: data flow summary -->
      <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-gray-200">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          <strong>Data flow:</strong>
          Visitor loads your page
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          Client GTM sends to your sGTM server
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          mbuzz tag sends to mbuzz API
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          Attribution calculated
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-amber-800">
      <strong>Already have sGTM?</strong> Skip to <a href="#step-3" class="underline font-medium">Step 3: Add the mbuzz tag</a>.
      Most agencies already have sGTM running — you just need to add the mbuzz tag template.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: Step-by-step setup -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Setup Guide</h2>

    <!-- ========== Step 1: Get sGTM hosting ========== -->
    <div id="step-1" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-purple-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">1</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Get an sGTM server</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="pl-14">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          You need a server to run your tags. The easiest option is <strong>Stape.io</strong> — it takes about 5 minutes,
          costs ~$10/month, and handles all the infrastructure for you. You'll get a subdomain on your
          own domain (like <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">gtm.yoursite.com</code>).
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
          <a href="https://stape.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="block border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-purple-300 hover:bg-purple-50 transition-colors">
            <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Stape.io</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-green-600 font-medium mb-2">Recommended</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Managed hosting. 5-min setup. Free tier available (10k requests/month).</div>
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.addingwell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="block border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-gray-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Addingwell</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">Managed hosting. EU-focused. Good for GDPR compliance.</div>
          </a>
          <a href="https://developers.google.com/tag-platform/tag-manager/server-side" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="block border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-gray-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Google Cloud</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 font-medium mb-2">DIY</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Self-hosted on GCP. More setup work. Best for large-scale deployments.</div>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong>What you'll have after this step:</strong> An sGTM container URL (like <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">https://gtm.yoursite.com</code>)
          and a GTM server container ID (like <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">GTM-XXXXXX</code>).
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ========== Step 2: Add client-side GTM ========== -->
    <div id="step-2" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">2</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Add client-side GTM to your website</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="pl-14">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          You need the regular Google Tag Manager snippet on your website. This is the piece that runs in the browser
          and sends data to your sGTM server. <strong>If you already have GTM on your site, skip this step</strong> —
          just make sure it's configured to send to your sGTM server.
        </p>

        <!-- Platform tabs -->
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-4">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200 px-4 py-3">
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Add the GTM snippet to your site:</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 text-sm mb-1">Webflow</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Project Settings &rarr; Custom Code &rarr; paste in Head section</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
              <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 text-sm mb-1">WordPress</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Install the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/duracelltomi-google-tag-manager/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">GTM4WP plugin</a> and enter your container ID</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
              <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 text-sm mb-1">Squarespace</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Settings &rarr; Developer Tools &rarr; Code Injection &rarr; paste in Header</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-4">
              <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-800 text-sm mb-1">Any other site</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Paste the GTM snippet into your HTML <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">&lt;head&gt;</code> tag. <a href="https://support.google.com/tagmanager/answer/6103696" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">Google's installation guide</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-blue-800">
          <strong>Important:</strong> Configure your client-side GTM container to send data to your sGTM server URL
          (from Step 1). In GTM, go to <strong>Admin</strong> &rarr; <strong>Container Settings</strong> &rarr; set the
          <strong>Server Container URL</strong> to your sGTM URL.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ========== Step 3: Add the mbuzz tag ========== -->
    <div id="step-3" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">3</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Add the mbuzz tag to your sGTM container</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="pl-14">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          This is where mbuzz gets connected. You'll import our tag template, then create one tag per call type.
          mbuzz uses a <strong>4-call model</strong>: Session, Event, Conversion, and Identify. Each tag is a separate
          instance of the same template with different settings.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg divide-y divide-gray-200">

          <!-- ===== Sub-step 3a: Import the template ===== -->
          <div class="p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">a</span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Import the mbuzz tag template</h4>
                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1.5">
                  <li>Open your <strong>server-side</strong> GTM container (not the client-side one)</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Templates</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
                  <li>Under Tag Templates, click <strong>Search Gallery</strong></li>
                  <li>Search for <strong>"mbuzz"</strong></li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Add to workspace</strong>, then <strong>Add</strong></li>
                </ol>
                <div class="mt-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-3 text-xs text-gray-500">
                  <strong>Manual import:</strong> Download from
                  <a href="https://github.com/mbuzzco/mbuzz-sgtm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">github.com/mbuzzco/mbuzz-sgtm</a>.
                  In GTM: Templates &rarr; New &rarr; Import &rarr; select the <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded">template.tpl</code> file.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- ===== Sub-step 3b: Session tag ===== -->
          <div class="p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">b</span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Create the Session tag</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
                  Fires on <strong>every page view</strong>. Creates visitors and sessions with full attribution (UTM params, referrer, channel).
                  This is the foundation — all other tags depend on it.
                </p>

                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1.5 mb-4">
                  <li>Go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
                  <li>Name it: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">mbuzz - Session</code></li>
                  <li>Tag type: <strong>mbuzz — Server-Side Attribution</strong></li>
                  <li>Fill in the fields:</li>
                </ol>

                <!-- Tag config visual -->
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
                  <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">sk_live_your_key_here</div>
                      </div>
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Session</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 italic">No other fields needed for Session tags. URL, referrer, and UTM params are captured automatically.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <ol start="5" class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                  <li>Set the <strong>Trigger</strong> to <strong>All Pages</strong> (the default Page View trigger)</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded p-3 text-xs text-green-700">
                  <strong>What this does:</strong> On every page view, the tag reads (or creates) a visitor ID cookie,
                  computes a device fingerprint, and calls <code class="bg-green-100 px-1 rounded">POST /api/v1/sessions</code>.
                  mbuzz extracts UTM params from the URL, classifies the traffic channel, and creates or continues a session.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- ===== Sub-step 3c: Event tag ===== -->
          <div class="p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 bg-green-100 text-green-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">c</span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Create Event tags</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-3">
                  Track mid-funnel actions: form submissions, button clicks, video plays, add-to-cart, etc.
                  Create one tag per event type, or use a GTM variable for the event name.
                </p>

                <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1.5 mb-4">
                  <li>Go to <strong>Tags</strong> &rarr; <strong>New</strong></li>
                  <li>Name it: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">mbuzz - Event - Form Submit</code> (use your event name)</li>
                  <li>Tag type: <strong>mbuzz — Server-Side Attribution</strong></li>
                  <li>Fill in the fields:</li>
                </ol>

                <!-- Tag config visual -->
                <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-4 mb-4">
                  <div class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Tag Configuration</div>
                  <div class="space-y-3">
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">API Key <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 font-mono">sk_live_your_key_here</div>
                      </div>
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Call Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">Event</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Event Type <span class="text-red-400">*</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700">form_submit</div>
                      </div>
                      <div>
                        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Custom Properties <span class="text-gray-400">(optional)</span></div>
                        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 rounded px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-400 italic">form_name = Contact Us</div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <ol start="5" class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                  <li>Set the <strong>Trigger</strong> to your custom event (e.g. a <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">form_submit</code> custom event trigger)</li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Advanced Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Tag Sequencing</strong></li>
                  <li>Check <strong>"Fire a tag before this tag fires"</strong> &rarr; select <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">mbuzz - Session</code></li>
                  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded p-3 text-xs text-blue-700">
                  <strong>Tag sequencing is critical.</strong> The Session tag must fire before any Event tag. Without it,
                  mbuzz doesn't know who the visitor is, and the event will be rejected.
                </div>

                <div class="mt-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-3 text-xs text-gray-500">
