  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">How It Works Under the Hood</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">You don't need to know this to use the integration. But if you're curious about what the mbuzz tag actually does:</p>

    <!-- Visual: What happens on each page view -->
    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200 px-6 py-3">
        <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-700">What happens on every page view</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">1</div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">Cookie check</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Tag looks for the <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">_mbuzz_vid</code> cookie. If it's a new visitor, generates a random 64-character ID and sets the cookie (first-party, 2-year expiry, HttpOnly).</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">2</div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">Device fingerprint</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Computes a fingerprint from the visitor's IP and browser: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">SHA256(ip|user_agent)</code>. This is how mbuzz links sessions to the same device.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">3</div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">Session creation</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Sends the visitor ID, page URL, referrer, and fingerprint to mbuzz. The server extracts UTM parameters, classifies the traffic channel (paid search, organic, social, etc.), and creates or continues a session.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">4</div>
            <div>
              <div class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">Attribution</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">When a conversion fires, mbuzz looks at all sessions for that visitor and calculates multi-touch attribution credit across channels.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Channel attribution -->
    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200 px-6 py-3">
        <h3 class="font-medium text-gray-700">Automatic channel classification</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6">
